<br>
Sad, but true.  My rogue was parked at the group the other night while the druid had free reign of the entire zone.<br>
<br>
I don't even carry the res stick on the rogue anymore on raids for emergency CR.  It goes in the druid's bag, since she has a much higher chance of survival.<br>
<br>
Shadow Knights with the instant-cast invis item from a green dungeon are superior in many stealth areas as well.  Imagine being able to click hide on-the-run without stopping.  Think of the advantages to pulling.  That's what Shadow Knights do now.<br>
<br>
We've already lost many of our stealth advantages.  Other classes do it better.<br>
<br>
The evade nerf is going to be a disaster for high level uber mob raids.  Taking the rogue down 2-3 places means you will be back at the top by your next BS.  Assuming evade is even succesful.  And not interrupted while you are getting pounded.<br>
<br>
I really think Verant needs to take a close look at exact aggro numbers each class is accumulating in these encounters before they even consider this nerf.  I'm willing to bet even a non-procing rogue will be at the top almost constantly for the full duration of a fight.  Evade was the only thing keeping us alive for more than a few backstabs.  Add in one or two other rogues, and it's a death spiral.  More than 2 rogues becomes a handicap.<br>
<br>
<br>
Master of Stealth: no more.  Improved invis and instant-cast items and spell-invis crossing zones kills this.<br>
Master of Damage: no more.  We'll either be dead or have auto-attack off, praying the hide button pops up again before we die.<br>
Master of picking pockets: woot!?<br>
Master of unlocking doors: woot!?<br>
<br>
I'm finding it very hard to believe that nerfing evade is in the interest of class balance.<br>
<br>
It won't affect a single thing in normal single-group situations.  It WILL affect everything in multi-group uber mob raids.  In which case it's a nerf to uber encounters, and rogues are just a sad victim of consequence.<br>
<br>
<br>
Just fix sneak/hide across zone lines, leave the rest.  Thanks.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulatro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Latro</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/01 5:08:03 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Changes to what we are proposing to Evade +more.</span><hr size=1> These changes boil down as follows:<br>
<br>
* On epic encounters, the rogue needs to avoid getting attacked in the first place.  It was easier when we dropped down further on the Hate list, so we'll have to be more careful.<br>
<br>
* On experience grinds, pity the poor tank trying to keep agro.  They already had problems even with "good" evade.  Learn root-prox agro.  Love root-prox agro.<br>
<br>
* The "small percentage" of pre-evade is the critical unknown here.  The previous proposal put it at 33%.  If the pre-evade percentage is too small, rogues will be bouncing from prime-agro to next in line all through the fights.<br>
<br>
As an aside, unless I am mistaken, this change to evade would have been a significant nerf even before Velious, so has little to do with expanded hate lists.<br>
<br>
By the way, how does Jolt work?<br>
<br>
