Be very careful you are very close to destroying one of the only blanced classes in eq and it took you 2 years to get us here. Heheh I thought this was tuning week. WTF can you possible give up so much to the other classes and then propose a gigantic nerf to another. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ruccus>Ruccus</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/01 6:35:38 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://pages.sprint.ca/deanweb/files/PUCKSMALL.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Changes to what we are proposing to Evade +more.</span><hr size=1> I was just reading some of the other posts, and they have brought up a good point - in the method suggested of evading down to between second and third on the list, a group with multiple rogues would in effect be helping to kill each other.<br>
<br>
If 2 or more rogues with similar weapons were attacking a mob, they would quickly start to outpace the hate of everyone else - meaning whoever evades sends the mob onto the other rogue instead of the tank. The new top person on the hate list would be the second rogue.  If the second rogue evades, the first rogue is back on the top of the hate list. This was the reason evade was implemented in the first place, to help get the mob onto the tank.<br>
<br>
I think the percentage method would be better, as it will always decrease hate on a success, and doesn't penalize a group for having more than one rogue.  We need to find a way to evade that doesn't affect other rogues attacking the same mob.<br>
<br>
R.R.<br>
Dwarven Miner 628 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=anaia>Anaia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/01 6:36:53 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Geez...come on~!</span><hr size=1> Let's make one thing very clear before we go any further with discussions about anything rogue related.  Evade would NOT have been topic of conversation by so many had you not mentioned the proposed change.<br>
