<br>
Finally, the lack of willingness to implement code changes (significant or not) to provide a game change to either balance/polish or enhance game play is exactly what angers your paying customers.  Furthermore, the idea that you have to go back and make a change to something that was intened to function a specific way to begin with and thus requires code changes to make it happen certainly illustrates your capabilities to make our suggestions happen and only serves to bolster the frustration felt when ideas are shot down because they would require effort, work and a genuine concern for the reasonable and majority ideas of a given class or community of players.<br>
<br>
I am not so out of touch with product development as to not understand that at some point you guys have to wrap things up call something 'complete' and begin working on new challenges and products.  Maybe if you would just have the guts to say....&quot;Hey, EQ Gamers.  We are trying to finish all the balance and polishing so that we can make EQ 2.  Get off our backs about this stuff because you wont get what you want&quot; people could actually respect and UNDERSTAND what you are doing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=anaia>Anaia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/01 6:40:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Oops...forgot my point.</span><hr size=1> My point that I was going to make before getting into a rant was that w/o Evade monopolizing the discussions, all the other issues that you have basically chosen to ignore or say you dont have time or desire to change would be all up in your faces.  How can you possibly ignore the fact that SO many rogues have all said the same stinking things about Poisions stacking....hide/sneak across zones...blah blah blah.  Geez.  It's amazing that people still bother writing at all. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urogarr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rogarr</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/01 6:40:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Changes to what we are proposing to Evade +more.</span><hr size=1> Dude wtf are you doing to the Rogue Class? Ok now your Evade &quot;fix&quot; might work if there is only 1 rogue fighting a mob if there are 2 might as well kiss one or both of them goodbye. This is nothing but Verant using a sledgehammer to squash a mosquito.<br>
